Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A method comprising, by a computing system: receiving, from a client device associated with a user, a first user request; accessing an instructional file, wherein the instructional file comprises one or more binary inference engines and one or more encrypted model data corresponding to the one or more binary inference engines, respectively; selecting, based on the first user request, a first binary inference engine from the one or more binary inference engines in the accessed instructional file; sending, to a licensing server, a validation request for a permission to execute the first binary inference engine; receiving the permission from the licensing server; decrypting, by a decryption key, the encrypted model data corresponding to the first binary inference engine; executing the first binary inference engine based on the first user request and the decrypted model data; and sending, to the client device responsive to the first user request, one or more execution results responsive to the execution of the first binary inference engine. 2. The method of Claim 1, wherein each of the one or more binary inference engines and its respective encrypted model data are associated by a linker. 3. The method of one of Claims 1-2, wherein each of the one or more binary inference engines comprises one or more machine-learning models. 4. The method of Claim 3, wherein the encrypted model data corresponding to the binary inference engine comprises one or more of: parameters associated with the one or more machine-learning models; weights associated with the one or more machine-learning models; declared syntaxes associated with the one or more machine-learning modes; or 

 descriptions associated with the one or more machine-learning models. 5. The method of one of Claims 3-4, wherein the one or more machine-learning models are based on neural networks. 6. The method of one of Claims 1-5, wherein each of the one or more encrypted model data is generated based on an encryption key. 7. The method of one of Claims 1-6, wherein the decryption key comprises a unique identifier associated with the computing system. 8. The method of Claim 7, wherein the unique identifier associated with the computing system comprises one or more of a hardware identifier or a media access control (MAC) address. 9. The method of one of Claims 1-8, wherein each of the one or more inference engines is associated with an expiration condition. 10. The method of Claim 9, wherein the expiration condition is based on one or more of time or a number of executions completed by the binary inference engine. 11. The method of one of Claims 1-10, wherein each of the one or more binary inference engines comprises one or more components. 12. The method of Claim 11, further comprising: determining one or more of the one or more components of the first binary inference engine to parallelize. 13. The method of Claim 12, wherein executing the first binary inference engine comprises executing the determined components of the first binary inference engine in parallel. 14. The method of one of Claims 1-13, wherein the first binary inference engine is associated with a public key, and wherein the validation request comprises the public key. 15. The method of Claim 14, wherein the permission is generated based on a validation of the public key by the licensing server. 16. The method of one of Claims 1-15, wherein the decryption key is issued by the licensing server. 17. The method of one of Claims 1-16, wherein the first user request is received from an application installed on the client device, and wherein executing the first binary inference engine is responsive to a first compilation of the application. 18. The method of Claim 17, further comprising: receiving, from the application installed on the client device associated with the user, a second user request; accessing the instructional file; selecting, based on the second user request, a second binary inference engine from the one or more binary inference engines in the accessed instructional file; sending, to the licensing server, a validation request for a permission to execute the second binary inference engine; receiving the permission from the licensing server; decrypting, by the decryption key, the encrypted model data corresponding to the second binary inference engine; executing the second binary inference engine based on the second user request and the decrypted model data responsive to the first compilation of the application; and sending, to the client device responsive to the second user request, one or more execution results responsive to the execution of the second binary inference engine. 19. One or more computer-readable non-transitory storage media embodying software that is operable when executed to: receive, from a client device associated with a user, a first user request; 

 access an instructional file, wherein the instructional file comprises one or more binary inference engines and one or more encrypted model data corresponding to the one or more binary inference engines, respectively; select, based on the first user request, a first binary inference engine from the one or more binary inference engines in the accessed instructional file; send, to a licensing server, a validation request for a permission to execute the first binary inference engine; receive the permission from the licensing server; decrypt, by a decryption key, the encrypted model data corresponding to the first binary inference engine; execute the first binary inference engine based on the first user request and the decrypted model data; and send, to the client device responsive to the first user request, one or more execution results responsive to the execution of the first binary inference engine. 20. A system comprising: one or more processors; and a non-transitory memory coupled to the processors comprising instructions executable by the processors, the processors operable when executing the instructions to: receive, from a client device associated with a user, a first user request; access an instructional file, wherein the instructional file comprises one or more binary inference engines and one or more encrypted model data corresponding to the one or more binary inference engines, respectively; select, based on the first user request, a first binary inference engine from the one or more binary inference engines in the accessed instructional file; send, to a licensing server, a validation request for a permission to execute the first binary inference engine; receive the permission from the licensing server; decrypt, by a decryption key, the encrypted model data corresponding to the first binary inference engine; 

 execute the first binary inference engine based on the first user request and the decrypted model data; and send, to the client device responsive to the first user request, one or more execution results responsive to the execution of the first binary inference engine.
